8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 186, L.D. 286, “An Act to Allow County
10 Commissioners Greater Flexibility When Establishing a Payment Schedule for
11 Municipalities to Pay County Tax Bills”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in §706 in the first indented paragraph in the 6th and 7th
13 lines (page 1, lines 10 and 11 in L.D.) by striking out the following: ", which may include
14 quarterly, biannual or other due dates"
15 Amend the bill in section 1 in §706 in the first indented paragraph in the 7th line (page
16 1, line 11 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "by which final payment of the tax must
17 be made"
18 Amend the bill in section 1 in §706 in the 2nd indented paragraph in the first line (page
19 1, line 13 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "final"
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment removes the provisions added to current law that describe due date
2244 intervals for payment of the county tax. The amendment also strikes the 2 provisions
2255 referencing the final payment of the county tax.
